1401.name: The Herta

stats.BaseSpeed: Base Speed (With Hyperspeed Action Advancer or 4P Mourning Collapse)   |   134 Speed (Generic Endgame Breakpoint)   |   160 Speed (Higher Endgame Speed Breakpoint)   |   Also worth mentioning is that Jade, one of The Herta's more powerful teammates, will grant her 30 Speed which also needs to be taken into account.

1401.playstyle:
Is The Herta Worth Building?
The Herta is an Erudition DPS that can perform extremely well across all general and Endgame content, especially when up against five enemies. She also has the nifty ability to locate Treasure Chests around the map.

If you already have a lot of limited Erudition units in your collection, The Herta isn't a must-pull. However, The Herta can synergize well with your other Erudition units, and pulling for her will still be worth it.


Should I Get The Herta's Light Cone?
The Herta's signature Light Cone, Into the Unreachable Veil, is a quality of life upgrade for her. Into the Unreachable Veil provides a lot of Skill DMG bonus and restores a Skill Point whenever The Herta uses an Ultimate.

While a great Light Cone to have, should you choose not to get Into the Unreachable Veil, The Herta can make do with other Light Cones such as Today Is Another Peaceful Day and Geniuses' Repose.


The Herta Gameplay Guide


Talent Increases DMG Based on Interpretation:
While The Herta is on your team, enemies will receive Interpretation stacks whenever they are attacked, up to a cap of 42. Each stack of Interpretation increases the damage the targets take.

If there is another Erudition character in a team with The Herta, enemies take even more damage.


Restore Energy with Allied Attacks:
The Herta can have her energy restored through allies attacking enemies. The more enemies each ally has hit, the more energy The Herta receives.

With this in mind, units that attack frequently and can attack all enemies are best used with The Herta.


Ultimate Redistributes Interpretation Stacks:
When The Herta uses her Ultimate, she deals Ice damage to all enemies, while also redistributing all Interpretation stacks. More powerful enemies will receive more stacks of Interpretation.

After using The Herta's Ultimate, she will gain an Inspiration stack, which enhances her next Skill.


Skill Deals DMG Based on Interpretation:
When The Herta uses her Skill, she will deal damage to her target and adjacent enemies.

Additionally, if she uses has an Inspiration stack, her Skill will deal additional damage based on the number of Interpretation stacks on the primary target. The primary target's Interpretation stacks will then reset.


Technique Marks Chests on the Map:
When Herta uses her Technique, any undiscovered Chests on the map will be marked.

Additionally, when used in the Simulated Universe or Divergent Universe, The Herta will deal damage to all enemies at the start of each wave. This damage is based on a percentage of their Max HP.

1410.name: Hysilens
1410.playstyle:
Should I Pull for Hysilens?
Hysilens is one of the best DoT units to be released in the game. Her ability to debuff enemies and deal DoT DMG makes her a great upgrade for DoT teams.

That being said, we only recommend getting Hysilens if you also have, or are planning to pull for Kafka to deal the most damage possible. Without Kafka, Hysilens cannot contend with other high tier units.


Should I Pull for Hysilens' Light Cone?
Hysilens' Light Cone, Why Does the Ocean Sing, provides Effect Hit Rate and can increase the enemy's DMG received from DoTs. This also provides a SPD increase that can be used by other allies when they attack an enemy.

While this is Hysilens' best-in-slot Light COne, you can consider skipping this for other Light Cones like Eyes of the Prey or any other DoT-related Light Cone. Instead, we recommend getting her E1 as this provides a better DMG increase for Hysilens.


Hysilens Gameplay Guide

Talent Inflicts Random DoTs:
When Hysilens uses her Basic ATK, Skill, or Ultimate, she can inflict different DoTs onto enemies.


Skill Increases DMG Taken by Enemies:
Hysilen's Skill deals AoE DMG and increases the DMG taken by enemies.


Ultimate Unleashes a Zone that Reduces DEF:
Hysilens' Ultimate summons a Zone and deals DMG to all enemies.

Enemies in Hysilens' Zone will have reduced DEF and take more Physical DoT DMG from Hysilens whenever they get hit by DoTs.

Technique Prevents Enemy Attacks:
Hysilens Technique summons a Dimension that will prevent enemies from attacking you.

When Hysilens attacks enemies affected by her Technique, her Talent will trigger multiple times and randomly applying DoTs to enemies.

1413.name: Evernight
1413.playstyle:
Should You Pull for Evernight?

Evernight is a Remembrance unit that is a DPS that can also buff other Memosprites. She can deal damage to all enemies and provides CRIT DMG buffs geared toward Memosprites.



With her Memosprite buffs being a key feature, Evernight works best with other Remembrance units, with Castorice benefiting the most from her kit. If you main Castorice and want her to be stronger or are in need of an Ice DPS, Evernight is worth pulling for!



Should You Pulll for Evernight's Light Cone?

To Evernight's Stars is designed for Evernight for its HP stat and Energy Regen. This enhances Evernight's support capabilities since it helps other Memosprites deal more damage to enemies.



While nice to have, you can use The Flower Remembers or Sweat Now, Cry Less as cheaper alternative options. You can also use The Story's Next Page or Victory in a Blink simply as stat sticks.



Evernight Build

Evernight is best built as a DPS unit that can also provide support to the party. World-Remaking Deliverer and Bone Collection's Serene Demesne are Evernight's best relics for the party-wide DMG buff and HP stats.



Prioritize CRIT DMG on Evernight since her buffs scale on that stat, and she can get the CRIT Rate from her Dark the Night, Still the Moon Bonus Ability and Trace Nodes. Since Evernight's Memosprite already has a Base SPD of 160, it is unnecessary to build SPD for this character.



Is a Memosprite Buffer

Evernight can increase Memosprite CRIT DMG when she is in the party. This buff becomes stronger the more ally memosprites there are on the field.



This makes Evernight a great Support for Remembrance units!



Accumulate Memoria Stacks with Skill

Evernight's Skill will summon Evey; her Memosprite. Evernight will also gain Memoria stacks through her Skill, which increases the damage dealt by Evey.



After collecting enough Memoria stacks, Evey will take action and deal damage to all enemies.



Gain Memoria by Losing HP

When Evernight or Evey loses HP, Memoria stacks will be accumulated.



Enter an Enhanced State with Ultimate

Evernight's Ultimate can deal DMG to all enemies and both her and Evey will enter an Enhanced State called the Darkest Riddle.



During Darkest Riddle, Evernight and Evey can deal increased damage and the Skill will be enhanced to gain Extra Memoria stacks.



Increase Ally CRIT DMG with Technique

Evernight's Technique increases the CRIT DMG of all ally memosprites and gain extra Memoria stacks at the start of combat.
